The paper discusses the use of hyperbolic embeddings in machine learning and natural language processing, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The focus on learning low-rank factorizations of hyperbolic embeddings suggests a stronger connection to cs.LG and cs.AI, but the potential applications in natural language processing and computer vision also make cs.CL and cs.CV plausible sub-categories.
